David J. Lesar

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search



David J. Lesar


Born
David John Lesar
May 30, 1953[1]
Madison, Wisconsin, U.S.


Residence
Houston, Texas, U.S.


Alma mater
University of Wisconsin–Madison (B.S./M.B.A.)


Occupation
Businessman &
Chairman at
Halliburton (2017-)


Salary
US$ 6,300,000 (2009)
Total: US$ 17,023,500 (2007)[2]


Predecessor
Dick Cheney


David John Lesar is an American businessman who is the Chairman of Halliburton Energy Services. He was the CEO of Halliburton for 17 years from 2000 to 2017. Trained as a Certified Public Accountant, Lesar spent 16 years at Arthur Andersen. He had spent most of his career at Andersen, where he worked on their Halliburton account. In 1995, Lesar was hired by Halliburton as a new vice president.



